1
00:00:12,117 --> 00:00:14,786
HYEONJUNG ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
YEAR 1, CLASS 3

2
00:00:30,301 --> 00:00:31,594
YOON SE-A

3
00:00:31,678 --> 00:00:33,054
KIM U-JIN

4
00:00:33,138 --> 00:00:37,809
WE DO NOT CLIMB ON THE WINDOWS!

5
00:00:41,938 --> 00:00:44,774
OUR DREAMS

6
00:00:52,157 --> 00:00:54,909
OUR AMAZING HAND TREE

7
00:01:12,844 --> 00:01:17,849
HOME OF THE HEART

8
00:01:20,101 --> 00:01:21,102
<i>Mom.</i>

9
00:01:22,395 --> 00:01:23,563
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

10
00:01:26,065 --> 00:01:27,942
<i>I want to live.</i>

11
00:01:29,527 --> 00:01:31,696
<i>But to live, I think I need to die.</i>

12
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:36,492
<i>You'll understand if you read my diary.</i>

13
00:01:41,289 --> 00:01:42,290
<i>Mom.</i>

14
00:01:44,417 --> 00:01:46,127
<i>Don't ever forgive that person.</i>

15
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:26,417
Ms. Choi Ji-seon?

16
00:02:28,795 --> 00:02:30,505
You must not have heard.

17
00:02:30,588 --> 00:02:33,174
The teachers have
a psychological evaluation today.

18
00:02:33,758 --> 00:02:36,803
It's almost time.
Please head over to the exam room.

19
00:02:46,521 --> 00:02:48,106
You must have been tidying up.

20
00:02:51,734 --> 00:02:52,735
Yes.

21
00:03:16,342 --> 00:03:20,138
All elementary school teachers nationwide
will be taking part in this evaluation.

22
00:03:20,221 --> 00:03:23,391
The outcome will not result
in any disadvantages.

23
00:03:23,474 --> 00:03:26,060
So please complete it honestly.

24
00:03:28,187 --> 00:03:30,231
3. I'M DOING RELATIVELY WELL
NOT AT ALL

25
00:03:33,651 --> 00:03:35,695
<i>Have you been</i>
<i>to the Korean medicine clinic?</i>

26
00:03:37,322 --> 00:03:38,156
Pardon?

27
00:03:39,282 --> 00:03:40,533
About your face.

28
00:03:41,367 --> 00:03:43,244
It seems to have gotten worse.

29
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:46,748
Ms. Choi.

30
00:03:47,248 --> 00:03:51,586
Following your psychological evaluation,
you will not be teaching from tomorrow.

31
00:03:52,962 --> 00:03:54,464
You said no disadvantages.

32
00:03:55,423 --> 00:03:57,884
There isn't a single
elementary school teacher

33
00:03:57,967 --> 00:04:00,303
who hasn't dealt with
stress or depression.

34
00:04:00,386 --> 00:04:03,431
You're basically telling her
to give up on being a teacher.

35
00:04:04,390 --> 00:04:05,433
But still,

36
00:04:05,516 --> 00:04:07,518
wouldn't it be better than dying?

37
00:04:15,818 --> 00:04:19,489
Ms. Choi, you will take
a temporary leave of absence

38
00:04:21,115 --> 00:04:22,784
as ordered by the ERPB.

39
00:04:29,457 --> 00:04:31,918
LET'S BECOME A GOOD TEACHER!

40
00:04:34,337 --> 00:04:36,047
TOMORROW I'LL MEET THE CHILDREN

41
00:04:36,130 --> 00:04:38,341
My daughter
is an elementary school teacher.

42
00:04:38,424 --> 00:04:39,634
UPHOLD U-JIN'S SELF-ESTEEM

43
00:04:39,717 --> 00:04:41,386
I was scared for her.

44
00:04:41,886 --> 00:04:45,473
These kinds of things were written
in her diary.

45
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:50,395
Please save my daughter.

46
00:04:57,151 --> 00:05:01,239
WILL IT END IF I DIE?

47
00:05:01,322 --> 00:05:06,119
TEACH YOU A LESSON

48
00:05:06,202 --> 00:05:08,371
HYEONJUNG ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

49
00:05:08,454 --> 00:05:11,707
What will happen to me now?

50
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:14,001
You need to get treatment first.

51
00:05:14,085 --> 00:05:16,379
Your mother

52
00:05:16,462 --> 00:05:20,341
brought your things in earlier.

53
00:05:20,425 --> 00:05:23,219
Does my mom know… about this too?

54
00:05:23,803 --> 00:05:26,472
Your mother came to the ERPB.

55
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:31,853
The best thing you can do for your mother
is to get good treatment.

56
00:05:31,936 --> 00:05:33,062
Shall we?

57
00:05:35,106 --> 00:05:38,734
Do you know what will happen
to my class and my students?

58
00:05:38,818 --> 00:05:42,071
Another teacher will take over from you.

59
00:05:42,155 --> 00:05:44,657
No, they can't.
Like me, that teacher will also--

60
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:47,076
You don't have to worry about that.

61
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:49,912
The new teacher

62
00:05:50,455 --> 00:05:52,623
is extremely terrifying.

63
00:06:06,679 --> 00:06:08,347
NA HWA-JIN

64
00:06:08,431 --> 00:06:10,224
Everyone, shall we sit down?

65
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:12,935
Attention!

66
00:06:13,019 --> 00:06:15,480
Kids, now's not the time for tag.

67
00:06:16,898 --> 00:06:18,024
Quiet!

68
00:06:21,611 --> 00:06:23,112
Class!

69
00:06:30,703 --> 00:06:31,787
Sir!

70
00:06:32,371 --> 00:06:36,334
If you and our tae kwon do master
got into a fight, who would win?

71
00:06:36,417 --> 00:06:38,377
Sir, can you beat Naruto?

72
00:06:38,461 --> 00:06:40,588
Sir, I need to use the bathroom.

73
00:06:40,671 --> 00:06:42,006
It's not bathroom time now.

74
00:06:42,089 --> 00:06:43,007
Sir.

75
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:45,551
-I told you to wait, didn't I?
-Bathroom, sir.

76
00:06:45,635 --> 00:06:47,011
What's wrong? Huh?

77
00:06:47,094 --> 00:06:48,721
No, not your pants. Wait!

78
00:06:56,896 --> 00:06:57,813
Sir.

79
00:06:58,856 --> 00:07:00,066
Bathroom.

80
00:07:05,863 --> 00:07:07,156
Me too!

81
00:07:09,825 --> 00:07:11,244
Super fun!

82
00:07:12,286 --> 00:07:14,664
Yay, so fun!

83
00:07:15,957 --> 00:07:17,875
You should have <i>gyeran-mari </i>for protein.

84
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:19,293
-Don't you want it?
-Tomatoes.

85
00:07:20,336 --> 00:07:21,629
Not a fan of tomatoes?

86
00:07:26,676 --> 00:07:27,843
Mr. Na.

87
00:07:27,927 --> 00:07:29,053
Yes.

88
00:07:29,136 --> 00:07:30,137
Please fold me a frog.

89
00:07:30,221 --> 00:07:33,224
It's not time to fold frogs.
Just do what I asked you to do.

90
00:07:33,307 --> 00:07:35,017
Please fold one for me.

91
00:07:35,101 --> 00:07:38,104
It's not time for frogs right now.
Just do as you're told.

92
00:07:43,693 --> 00:07:45,444
No, I wasn't mad at you.

93
00:07:45,945 --> 00:07:47,863
We flip this over again.

94
00:07:50,449 --> 00:07:52,618
Okay, just like this.

95
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:55,663
It's the shape of a frog's back legs.

96
00:07:55,746 --> 00:07:57,999
Yeon-seo, have you tried frog legs before?

97
00:07:58,082 --> 00:08:00,209
Yuck. Do people eat frog legs?

98
00:08:00,293 --> 00:08:01,919
I've tried them before.

99
00:08:02,003 --> 00:08:04,630
The frog is done!

100
00:08:04,714 --> 00:08:06,591
Hop! Wow.

101
00:08:06,674 --> 00:08:08,759
Make one for me too, please!

102
00:08:29,405 --> 00:08:30,406
Ga-yun.

103
00:08:30,906 --> 00:08:33,159
Was being a teacher this hard?

104
00:08:37,872 --> 00:08:40,374
Those damn frogs. I had to…

105
00:08:52,511 --> 00:08:53,929
LET'S BECOME A GOOD TEACHER!

106
00:08:54,013 --> 00:08:58,267
<i>Today, we're going to learn</i>
<i>how to express our feelings with words.</i>

107
00:08:58,351 --> 00:09:02,271
What do you say when you're feeling happy?

108
00:09:03,856 --> 00:09:04,732
That's right.

109
00:09:04,815 --> 00:09:07,443
"I'm in a good mood. I'm so happy."

110
00:09:08,069 --> 00:09:11,072
Just like this, we need to be able
to put our feelings into words.

111
00:09:11,155 --> 00:09:15,242
You always have to tell me
how you're feeling.

112
00:09:15,326 --> 00:09:16,369
Okay?

113
00:09:16,452 --> 00:09:19,789
It's nice to meet you. My name is…

114
00:09:24,210 --> 00:09:26,629
CHOI JI-SEON

115
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,843
Class!

116
00:09:32,927 --> 00:09:34,720
It's nice to meet you.

117
00:09:34,804 --> 00:09:37,890
My name is Choi Ji-seon.

118
00:09:40,601 --> 00:09:42,645
I hope we can get along well.

119
00:09:42,728 --> 00:09:44,188
You know who I am now, right?

120
00:09:44,772 --> 00:09:48,234
Can you please
introduce yourselves to me too?

121
00:09:48,317 --> 00:09:50,403
Yes!

122
00:09:50,486 --> 00:09:51,320
You can start.

123
00:09:52,697 --> 00:09:54,907
I am Kim Yong-hun.

124
00:09:57,410 --> 00:09:58,661
I am Lee Yeon-seo.

125
00:10:14,093 --> 00:10:15,344
You're Kim U-jin, right?

126
00:10:16,137 --> 00:10:17,471
It's all right. Take a seat.

127
00:10:18,889 --> 00:10:19,849
Applause.

128
00:10:23,144 --> 00:10:24,812
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

129
00:10:24,895 --> 00:10:27,481
-Bye. Thank you.
-Thank you.

130
00:10:27,565 --> 00:10:28,816
Take care, ma'am.

131
00:10:28,899 --> 00:10:30,192
See you tomorrow, U-jin.

132
00:10:30,276 --> 00:10:31,944
-Say goodbye, Hun.
-Goodbye.

133
00:10:32,528 --> 00:10:34,530
Please take good care of U-jin, Ms. Choi.

134
00:10:34,613 --> 00:10:36,907
I'll do my best.
You can trust me with him.

135
00:10:37,491 --> 00:10:41,746
If I have any questions or concerns
from time to time, may I contact you?

136
00:10:41,829 --> 00:10:43,038
Of course you can.

137
00:10:43,122 --> 00:10:45,916
If you install the Talk Mate app,
you can message or call me.

138
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:49,295
Please contact me there.
The hours are from eight to six.

139
00:10:50,254 --> 00:10:52,173
You live in Stern Complex, don't you?

140
00:10:53,174 --> 00:10:54,592
Yes, I do.

141
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:58,053
Thanks for today. Let's go, U-jin.

142
00:11:09,523 --> 00:11:13,068
<i>This is U-jin's mom.</i>
<i>I have a small concern.</i>

143
00:11:13,569 --> 00:11:18,073
<i>When you told U-jin to sit earlier,</i>
<i>you spoke very sternly.</i>

144
00:11:18,157 --> 00:11:22,411
<i>I'm worried U-jin might think</i>
<i>you don't like him.</i>

145
00:11:22,495 --> 00:11:24,997
<i>I'll do my best to make sure</i>
<i>he doesn't feel that way.</i>

146
00:11:30,294 --> 00:11:33,380
<i>I'm just worried his self-esteem</i>
<i>might drop. You understand, right?</i>

147
00:11:34,715 --> 00:11:35,549
Of course.

148
00:11:36,133 --> 00:11:39,678
<i>Request for Kim U-jin.</i>
<i>Make sure his self-esteem isn't affected.</i>

149
00:11:50,898 --> 00:11:52,566
You're not sure?

150
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:54,193
Should I explain again?

151
00:11:55,319 --> 00:11:57,321
Ms. Choi, I want to do it.

152
00:11:57,404 --> 00:11:58,906
I can do it too!

153
00:11:58,989 --> 00:12:00,616
I can do it too!

154
00:12:00,699 --> 00:12:02,326
Quiet.

155
00:12:07,039 --> 00:12:07,873
It's all right.

156
00:12:13,295 --> 00:12:15,089
<i>U-jin's self-esteem is falling,</i>

157
00:12:15,172 --> 00:12:17,591
<i>so don't make him do math</i>
<i>in front of the class.</i>

158
00:12:20,719 --> 00:12:24,223
<i>Please don't mark incorrect answers</i>
<i>with a slash on U-jin's spelling test.</i>

159
00:12:24,306 --> 00:12:26,058
<i>It's affecting his self-esteem.</i>

160
00:12:28,185 --> 00:12:32,773
<i>"Don't," "no," or "stop."</i>
<i>Please don't use these restrictive words.</i>

161
00:12:34,441 --> 00:12:38,070
<i>Please always take my child's side</i>
<i>in any conflicts with his peers.</i>

162
00:12:38,153 --> 00:12:42,074
<i>Please use an advisory or requesting tone</i>
<i>rather than a commanding one.</i>

163
00:12:42,157 --> 00:12:45,286
<i>When greeting, please don't make him bow</i>
<i>with his hands together.</i>

164
00:12:45,369 --> 00:12:48,998
<i>If he feels pressured to greet properly,</i>
<i>it will lower his self-esteem.</i>

165
00:12:49,081 --> 00:12:52,167
<i>Please don't scold children</i>
<i>for being noisy in the classroom.</i>

166
00:12:52,251 --> 00:12:53,919
<i>It will make them feel discouraged.</i>

167
00:13:18,277 --> 00:13:19,528
-You're overreacting.
-Yeah.

168
00:13:19,612 --> 00:13:21,280
-It's Ji-seon.
-Ji-seon!

169
00:13:23,407 --> 00:13:25,075
-I've missed you.
-It's been so long.

170
00:13:25,159 --> 00:13:25,993
Ji-seon.

171
00:13:29,747 --> 00:13:31,832
-Congratulations!
-When is the wedding?

172
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:34,043
-It's written in there. Take a look.
-Hold on.

173
00:13:34,126 --> 00:13:35,794
Won-ho can't seem to stop smiling.

174
00:13:35,878 --> 00:13:37,796
<i>Please wear a strapless bra.</i>

175
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:40,549
<i>It may negatively affect</i>
<i>the boys' sexual awareness.</i>

176
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:42,551
-Congratulations, Won-ho!
-Cheers!

177
00:13:42,635 --> 00:13:44,887
Cheers!

178
00:14:00,527 --> 00:14:04,073
<i>Why would you post something shameful</i>
<i>when the children might see it?</i>

179
00:14:04,156 --> 00:14:06,742
<i>I'm afraid it might provoke</i>
<i>their sexual curiosity.</i>

180
00:14:11,330 --> 00:14:13,874
How did she find my Instagram?

181
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:16,627
<i>You always seem to be out.</i>
<i>Don't you think of the children?</i>

182
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:19,046
<i>You spend your tax-funded salary</i>
<i>on having fun.</i>

183
00:14:19,129 --> 00:14:21,382
<i>Please invest in preparing for class too.</i>

184
00:14:21,465 --> 00:14:24,176
<i>I'd tolerate it</i>
<i>if it were at least about children.</i>

185
00:14:24,677 --> 00:14:27,471
But I think she's gone too far.
It's strictly personal.

186
00:14:28,973 --> 00:14:31,141
Change your account username.

187
00:14:31,225 --> 00:14:33,644
Actually, it'd be even better
if you didn't use it.

188
00:14:33,727 --> 00:14:35,896
Why should I?
I haven't done anything wrong.

189
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:38,565
I tried to take action at first too.

190
00:14:38,649 --> 00:14:40,859
I tried pressing charges
and persuading them.

191
00:14:40,943 --> 00:14:43,570
But in the end,
all I got was a group petition

192
00:14:43,654 --> 00:14:45,698
claiming I sided only with the teachers.

193
00:14:46,699 --> 00:14:48,951
No matter what I said,
they wouldn't listen.

194
00:14:49,034 --> 00:14:51,453
And no matter what I did,
they saw it negatively.

195
00:14:51,537 --> 00:14:53,580
In the end, they shook up

196
00:14:54,081 --> 00:14:55,374
the whole school.

197
00:15:02,131 --> 00:15:03,882
REMOVE "INSTAGRAM"?
DELETE APP

198
00:15:04,383 --> 00:15:05,801
DELETE "INSTAGRAM"?
DELETE

199
00:15:12,349 --> 00:15:15,352
<i>I'll use Instagram when I retire.</i>

200
00:15:15,853 --> 00:15:18,814
<i>I have the children to consider.</i>

201
00:16:16,038 --> 00:16:18,332
HOME OF THE HEART

202
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:53,867
U-jin.

203
00:16:55,661 --> 00:16:58,580
This is your Home of the Heart.

204
00:16:58,664 --> 00:17:00,833
You can have fun with your friends here.

205
00:17:06,463 --> 00:17:08,215
How do you feel?

206
00:17:08,715 --> 00:17:10,551
What do you look for in a friend?

207
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:14,054
I want to have fun together.

208
00:17:14,555 --> 00:17:15,556
Right?

209
00:17:15,639 --> 00:17:19,685
Since this is Home of the Heart,
you can do whatever your heart tells you.

210
00:17:20,185 --> 00:17:21,436
Should we try to do

211
00:17:21,979 --> 00:17:23,939
what your heart is telling you?

212
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:29,778
Oh, it's the back.

213
00:17:32,990 --> 00:17:34,741
Yes!

214
00:17:35,617 --> 00:17:36,743
Here's water.

215
00:17:36,827 --> 00:17:37,953
Thanks.

216
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,586
-Don't hurt yourself.
-Go, U-jin!

217
00:17:45,669 --> 00:17:46,628
Whoa!

218
00:17:49,214 --> 00:17:50,048
U-jin, well done!

219
00:17:50,132 --> 00:17:51,175
Yeah!

220
00:17:51,258 --> 00:17:52,467
Over here. Pass!

221
00:17:53,677 --> 00:17:55,929
Eun-ho kicks the ball.

222
00:17:56,013 --> 00:17:57,389
Over here. Pass!

223
00:17:58,098 --> 00:17:59,349
U-jin, pass!

224
00:18:01,351 --> 00:18:02,644
Hey, it went in.

225
00:18:03,812 --> 00:18:05,814
U-jin, I'm sorry.

226
00:18:08,317 --> 00:18:10,319
-Kim U-jin!
-<i>"Don't," "no," or "stop."</i>

227
00:18:10,402 --> 00:18:12,779
<i>Please don't use these restrictive words.</i>

228
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:16,909
<i>Please always take my child's side</i>
<i>in any conflicts with his peers.</i>

229
00:18:18,911 --> 00:18:21,038
That hurts.

230
00:18:21,121 --> 00:18:22,164
Mommy.

231
00:18:22,247 --> 00:18:23,540
U-jin!

232
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:31,131
Mommy!

233
00:18:31,882 --> 00:18:34,218
-It hurts.
-Seo-jun, are you okay?

234
00:18:34,968 --> 00:18:37,012
Mommy.

235
00:18:40,057 --> 00:18:41,558
Ladies.

236
00:18:42,476 --> 00:18:44,144
I'm sure you were alarmed.

237
00:18:44,645 --> 00:18:46,104
Please have some tea first.

238
00:18:54,905 --> 00:18:58,492
Seo-jun briefly told me what happened.

239
00:18:59,326 --> 00:19:02,537
They're boys, and when they play sports,

240
00:19:04,164 --> 00:19:05,624
they can get into fights.

241
00:19:05,707 --> 00:19:06,583
I understand.

242
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:09,086
Thank you for understanding.

243
00:19:09,169 --> 00:19:12,256
The children apologized
to each other and made up.

244
00:19:13,507 --> 00:19:15,384
Did you make U-jin apologize?

245
00:19:21,306 --> 00:19:23,850
He did something wrong.
Of course he has to apologize.

246
00:19:23,934 --> 00:19:27,562
U-jin told me Seo-jun pushed him first.

247
00:19:28,063 --> 00:19:30,524
Since Seo-jun started it,
only he should apologize.

248
00:19:33,068 --> 00:19:34,111
Ma'am.

249
00:19:34,945 --> 00:19:36,738
Seo-jun injured his eye.

250
00:19:36,822 --> 00:19:38,532
He almost went blind.

251
00:19:38,615 --> 00:19:40,701
U-jin was also hurt.

252
00:19:40,784 --> 00:19:43,745
He was so upset
that he came home and cried.

253
00:19:43,829 --> 00:19:46,206
You have a strange way of putting things.

254
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:49,126
Can't you see I'm trying to let it go
for our kids' sake?

255
00:19:49,209 --> 00:19:50,919
My child's feelings got hurt!

256
00:19:51,545 --> 00:19:53,755
What will you do if he's traumatized?

257
00:19:53,839 --> 00:19:57,009
He'd better not be.
I won't let your son get away with it.

258
00:19:57,092 --> 00:19:59,052
-What?
-Ladies.

259
00:19:59,136 --> 00:20:00,721
Please stop, and let's calm down.

260
00:20:00,804 --> 00:20:03,181
Ms. Choi, please say something.

261
00:20:03,265 --> 00:20:07,019
I heard U-jin couldn't even get along
with others in the beginning.

262
00:20:07,102 --> 00:20:09,229
Now I can see why.

263
00:20:09,313 --> 00:20:10,564
-Hey!
-"Hey"?

264
00:20:11,064 --> 00:20:13,900
Convene the School Violence Committee.
Try mouthing off there.

265
00:20:13,984 --> 00:20:15,777
All right. Fine!

266
00:20:15,861 --> 00:20:17,195
Bring it on. Convene it!

267
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:21,408
Ladies, please calm down.
I'm begging you. Please calm down.

268
00:20:22,075 --> 00:20:22,909
Ma'am.

269
00:20:23,410 --> 00:20:26,997
I feel a School Violence Committee meeting
would be unfavorable for U-jin.

270
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:28,248
Why don't we all just--

271
00:20:28,332 --> 00:20:30,917
Things have been blown out of proportion
because of you.

272
00:20:32,419 --> 00:20:35,797
I told you to take U-jin's side
in any conflicts with his peers,

273
00:20:35,881 --> 00:20:37,299
and you agreed to it.

274
00:20:38,008 --> 00:20:39,968
I never agreed to it.

275
00:20:41,636 --> 00:20:42,554
Pardon me?

276
00:20:43,638 --> 00:20:47,351
Why claim now you never agreed
when you were silent back then?

277
00:20:48,060 --> 00:20:50,228
I will speak to Seo-jun's mother--

278
00:20:50,312 --> 00:20:52,064
How will you testify at the meeting?

279
00:20:54,858 --> 00:20:56,026
Well…

280
00:20:57,444 --> 00:20:59,863
-I'll have to tell them what I saw.
-Right.

281
00:21:00,989 --> 00:21:02,407
So what did you see?

282
00:21:09,498 --> 00:21:10,665
Give me your number.

283
00:21:10,749 --> 00:21:13,460
It's against policy
to give out our personal phone numbers.

284
00:21:13,543 --> 00:21:15,962
-On Talk Mate--
-I can't call you there after work.

285
00:21:16,046 --> 00:21:18,423
You still want to enjoy
your post-work life

286
00:21:18,507 --> 00:21:20,467
after getting my child into trouble?

287
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,760
That's not what I mean.

288
00:21:21,843 --> 00:21:23,095
Give it to me!

289
00:21:31,311 --> 00:21:33,271
This is all your fault.

290
00:21:34,481 --> 00:21:35,607
Do you know what?

291
00:21:36,108 --> 00:21:38,693
My husband is furious about this.

292
00:21:39,194 --> 00:21:41,863
Should I call him right now? Should I?

293
00:21:43,365 --> 00:21:44,533
Ma'am.

294
00:21:45,575 --> 00:21:48,537
A homeroom teacher
cannot help you in that way.

295
00:22:05,637 --> 00:22:06,471
Hello?

296
00:22:06,555 --> 00:22:07,848
<i>This is U-jin's mom.</i>

297
00:22:08,849 --> 00:22:09,850
Ma'am.

298
00:22:10,642 --> 00:22:12,394
How did you get my number?

299
00:22:12,477 --> 00:22:15,897
<i>Is that important right now?</i>
<i>What are you going to do at the meeting?</i>

300
00:22:18,108 --> 00:22:19,484
<i>Hello? Answer me.</i>

301
00:22:19,568 --> 00:22:20,485
Well…

302
00:22:20,569 --> 00:22:22,195
U-JIN'S MOTHER

303
00:22:32,038 --> 00:22:32,998
<i>Hello?</i>

304
00:22:33,498 --> 00:22:34,332
<i>Ms. Choi!</i>

305
00:22:34,416 --> 00:22:35,625
Hello?

306
00:22:35,709 --> 00:22:38,003
<i>Why did you take so long to answer?</i>

307
00:22:39,004 --> 00:22:40,005
<i>Hello?</i>

308
00:22:42,257 --> 00:22:43,758
I'm sorry.

309
00:22:43,842 --> 00:22:45,469
U-JIN'S MOTHER

310
00:22:47,637 --> 00:22:48,847
<i>Are you listening to me?</i>

311
00:22:49,598 --> 00:22:51,057
<i>Why aren't you answering me?</i>

312
00:22:51,141 --> 00:22:54,186
I'm planning my lessons at the moment.

313
00:22:55,562 --> 00:22:56,730
U-JIN'S MOTHER

314
00:23:06,531 --> 00:23:08,742
U-JIN'S MOTHER

315
00:23:10,827 --> 00:23:12,078
U-JIN'S MOTHER

316
00:23:14,039 --> 00:23:16,958
<i>I told you to take U-jin's side</i>
<i>in any conflicts with his peers,</i>

317
00:23:17,042 --> 00:23:18,126
<i>and you agreed to it.</i>

318
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:20,462
<i>You still want to enjoy</i>
<i>your post-work life</i>

319
00:23:20,545 --> 00:23:22,631
<i>after getting my child into trouble?</i>

320
00:23:24,716 --> 00:23:25,592
U-JIN'S MOTHER

321
00:23:25,675 --> 00:23:27,594
<i>This is all your fault.</i>

322
00:23:27,677 --> 00:23:30,263
<i>And you agreed to it.</i>

323
00:23:31,181 --> 00:23:32,182
<i>Ms. Choi?</i>

324
00:23:33,183 --> 00:23:34,267
<i>Ms. Choi?</i>

325
00:23:39,856 --> 00:23:41,566
<i>This is all your fault.</i>

326
00:23:41,650 --> 00:23:45,654
<i>This is all your fault now.</i>

327
00:23:45,737 --> 00:23:48,031
<i>Ms. Choi!</i>

328
00:24:05,674 --> 00:24:06,925
<i>Ms. Choi.</i>

329
00:24:07,008 --> 00:24:09,135
<i>Why aren't you answering your phone?</i>

330
00:24:09,219 --> 00:24:11,096
<i>Are you avoiding me out of guilt?</i>

331
00:24:11,846 --> 00:24:13,557
<i>Let's talk in person.</i>

332
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:14,641
-<i>Okay?</i>
-Who is it?

333
00:24:17,894 --> 00:24:19,896
I'm just going out for a moment.

334
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:20,897
Where to?

335
00:24:23,066 --> 00:24:24,401
Where are you going?

336
00:24:25,610 --> 00:24:27,821
This is absurd.
How is U-jin the perpetrator?

337
00:24:28,572 --> 00:24:29,489
It's unacceptable.

338
00:24:29,573 --> 00:24:31,992
Why did the School Violence Committee
rule against us?

339
00:24:32,742 --> 00:24:34,286
It's Level 1 disciplinary action.

340
00:24:34,369 --> 00:24:36,621
All you need to do
is submit a written apology.

341
00:24:36,705 --> 00:24:38,164
It was you, wasn't it?

342
00:24:38,665 --> 00:24:41,001
-Pardon?
-You took their side, didn't you?

343
00:24:42,043 --> 00:24:43,920
You're mistaken. I didn't side with--

344
00:24:44,004 --> 00:24:46,089
Just because I said a few things,

345
00:24:46,172 --> 00:24:48,425
you went after U-jin out of spite,
didn't you?

346
00:24:52,887 --> 00:24:55,974
You don't deserve to be a teacher.

347
00:24:57,267 --> 00:24:59,894
I can't trust you with U-jin anymore,
so just quit.

348
00:24:59,978 --> 00:25:02,522
My husband is also enraged,

349
00:25:03,023 --> 00:25:04,441
so watch out.

350
00:25:37,807 --> 00:25:38,642
Dad?

351
00:25:50,278 --> 00:25:51,488
U-jin, come with me.

352
00:25:53,448 --> 00:25:54,658
Come on, Kim U-jin.

353
00:25:59,621 --> 00:26:00,622
I said come with me!

354
00:26:01,539 --> 00:26:03,875
We're in class right now.
If you come back later…

355
00:26:08,922 --> 00:26:11,508
Please don't do this. Think of U-jin.

356
00:26:16,805 --> 00:26:18,223
For God's sake.

357
00:26:18,890 --> 00:26:20,392
How pathetic. Seriously.

358
00:26:23,603 --> 00:26:24,437
Let's go.

359
00:26:25,271 --> 00:26:26,106
Move.

360
00:26:33,363 --> 00:26:34,614
Everyone, it's all right.

361
00:26:37,242 --> 00:26:38,868
It's okay, Ji-yeong. Don't cry.

362
00:26:45,458 --> 00:26:49,379
TEACHERS' RIGHTS PROTECTION COMMITTEE
NOTICE TO ATTEND

363
00:26:55,051 --> 00:26:56,469
<i>Do it if you want to.</i>

364
00:26:56,970 --> 00:27:00,390
Even if I violated teachers' rights,
all I have to do is apologize.

365
00:27:00,890 --> 00:27:02,559
Call a meeting on teachers' rights.

366
00:27:05,186 --> 00:27:08,231
I couldn't just sit back
when you abused your power.

367
00:27:12,652 --> 00:27:14,654
So I reported you for child abuse.

368
00:27:17,866 --> 00:27:20,827
You targeted U-jin,
humiliating him in front of others.

369
00:27:20,910 --> 00:27:24,372
And when I challenged this,
you gaslit a student to ostracize him.

370
00:27:24,456 --> 00:27:27,292
You lured him to a storage room
you call Home of the Heart

371
00:27:27,375 --> 00:27:28,752
and did unspeakable things--

372
00:27:28,835 --> 00:27:31,254
Ma'am, none of this is true.

373
00:27:31,337 --> 00:27:33,715
It's up to the police to look into that.

374
00:27:33,798 --> 00:27:36,551
Ma'am, I have never
emotionally abused a child.

375
00:27:38,178 --> 00:27:41,765
Do you think I made up a story
just to screw you over?

376
00:27:42,891 --> 00:27:44,893
What about how wronged U-jin feels?

377
00:27:45,685 --> 00:27:49,355
If you're innocent,
then why is U-jin crying at home?

378
00:27:49,439 --> 00:27:51,399
I feel for U-jin,

379
00:27:52,066 --> 00:27:53,276
but this isn't right.

380
00:27:53,359 --> 00:27:55,695
So why is the teacher
not taking responsibility

381
00:27:55,779 --> 00:27:57,822
when a student has been wronged?

382
00:27:57,906 --> 00:27:59,616
Is it my resignation

383
00:28:00,116 --> 00:28:01,451
that you want?

384
00:28:02,368 --> 00:28:04,204
I also consulted a lawyer.

385
00:28:04,287 --> 00:28:06,414
The law has changed.
Even if you report me,

386
00:28:06,915 --> 00:28:09,542
I won't be suspended immediately
like before.

387
00:28:09,626 --> 00:28:11,085
Who said anything about that?

388
00:28:11,586 --> 00:28:12,587
Teach your class.

389
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:15,423
When you're done,
give your statement to the police.

390
00:28:16,132 --> 00:28:18,593
Reaching a verdict
will take six months to a year.

391
00:28:18,676 --> 00:28:20,345
It'll take longer than you think.

392
00:28:20,845 --> 00:28:22,555
If you can't handle it, you can quit.

393
00:28:29,813 --> 00:28:32,565
If I'm found innocent,
what will you do then?

394
00:28:37,195 --> 00:28:38,822
Then I'll have to apologize.

395
00:28:39,864 --> 00:28:40,990
That's all.

396
00:28:41,491 --> 00:28:42,867
That's the law.

397
00:29:19,237 --> 00:29:20,280
<i>Ms. Choi.</i>

398
00:29:20,363 --> 00:29:23,449
<i>This came up on a moms' forum.</i>
<i>Have you seen it?</i>

399
00:29:23,533 --> 00:29:25,743
<i>It seems quite serious.</i>

400
00:29:26,953 --> 00:29:29,747
1-3 HOMEROOM TEACHER
AT HYEONJUNG ELEMENTARY IS A CHILD ABUSER

401
00:29:32,208 --> 00:29:33,710
LOOKS CAN BE DECEIVING
SO SHOCKING

402
00:29:35,837 --> 00:29:38,590
PLEASE SHARE THIS POST UNTIL THE DAY
CHOI JI-SEON IS PUNISHED

403
00:29:38,673 --> 00:29:39,716
MS. CHOI 010-0235-7462

404
00:29:50,727 --> 00:29:53,813
All right. Year 1, class 3,
please come in.

405
00:29:55,982 --> 00:29:56,900
Let's go, class.

406
00:30:03,072 --> 00:30:04,240
Have a watermelon slice.

407
00:30:10,788 --> 00:30:12,582
Is that all the rice you're having?

408
00:30:13,082 --> 00:30:15,168
Is that okay? Enjoy your meal.

409
00:30:17,086 --> 00:30:17,921
Scissors.

410
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,673
Scissors, scissors, rock.

411
00:30:21,925 --> 00:30:24,469
<i>We keep getting complaint calls.</i>

412
00:30:25,386 --> 00:30:27,931
<i>Many parents are coming in person too.</i>

413
00:30:28,848 --> 00:30:30,683
<i>They say if we let you come to work,</i>

414
00:30:31,434 --> 00:30:33,603
<i>they won't send their children to school.</i>

415
00:30:36,105 --> 00:30:37,398
<i>I'm sorry</i>

416
00:30:37,899 --> 00:30:40,234
<i>I can't tell you to hold out.</i>

417
00:31:20,274 --> 00:31:22,276
TEACHER
KIM U-JIN

418
00:31:26,114 --> 00:31:28,324
KIDDOS IN YEAR 1, CLASS 3

419
00:31:28,408 --> 00:31:29,826
KIM U-JIN: THOUGHTFUL, SMILEY

420
00:31:29,909 --> 00:31:31,244
KIM YUN-U: VERY CONSIDERATE

421
00:31:36,624 --> 00:31:39,752
MS. CHOI, BE HAPPY

422
00:31:43,506 --> 00:31:46,467
<i>She would've felt like</i>
<i>she was standing all alone in a jungle.</i>

423
00:31:46,551 --> 00:31:48,636
IT'S HARD TO OPEN MY EYES IN THE MORNING

424
00:31:49,220 --> 00:31:50,972
Eyes were on her from all sides,

425
00:31:51,472 --> 00:31:54,308
with people ready to pounce on her.

426
00:31:55,852 --> 00:31:57,729
There was no one or weapon to help her.

427
00:31:57,812 --> 00:31:59,522
I'M MAKING MY OWN STUDENTS UNHAPPY

428
00:31:59,605 --> 00:32:00,440
WILL IT END IF I DIE?

429
00:32:00,523 --> 00:32:02,358
Why are the police investigating this?

430
00:32:02,442 --> 00:32:04,944
It's all perfectly reasonable
and legitimate guidance.

431
00:32:05,528 --> 00:32:08,114
The police have to investigate
since a report was filed.

432
00:32:08,197 --> 00:32:10,700
Can they report it
when it's clearly unreasonable?

433
00:32:10,783 --> 00:32:12,243
Yes, they can.

434
00:32:12,326 --> 00:32:13,453
They can?

435
00:32:13,536 --> 00:32:16,539
For child abuse, you can file a report
based solely on suspicion.

436
00:32:18,791 --> 00:32:20,043
As you can see,

437
00:32:20,126 --> 00:32:24,922
11,626 teachers
have been reported for child abuse

438
00:32:25,006 --> 00:32:27,467
over the past several years.

439
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:30,386
But only 1.6% of them

440
00:32:30,470 --> 00:32:32,180
were actually prosecuted.

441
00:32:33,056 --> 00:32:37,727
This means most of the teachers suffered
because of the reports,

442
00:32:38,352 --> 00:32:41,397
even though their guidance was legitimate.

443
00:32:41,481 --> 00:32:44,317
Since you can report
based on suspicion alone,

444
00:32:44,817 --> 00:32:48,112
you won't be punished
for a false accusation

445
00:32:48,196 --> 00:32:50,031
even if the accused is found innocent.

446
00:32:50,573 --> 00:32:52,492
That's what the parents are abusing.

447
00:32:52,575 --> 00:32:53,993
They press charges first,

448
00:32:54,869 --> 00:32:57,038
and if the verdict is innocent,
they dismiss it.

449
00:32:57,121 --> 00:32:58,247
Damn it.

450
00:32:58,331 --> 00:33:03,086
Emotional abuse is difficult to define
under current child abuse laws

451
00:33:03,169 --> 00:33:05,046
because the harm isn't visible.

452
00:33:06,380 --> 00:33:08,508
You can only rely on what the parents say.

453
00:33:08,591 --> 00:33:10,968
It's difficult for teachers
to prove it's not abuse.

454
00:33:11,052 --> 00:33:13,054
And they get worn down alone.

455
00:33:13,137 --> 00:33:15,389
Most of them will be found innocent,

456
00:33:15,473 --> 00:33:18,059
but until then,
they have to be investigated

457
00:33:18,142 --> 00:33:20,520
and, in some cases,
be removed from their class.

458
00:33:20,603 --> 00:33:24,857
Teachers are told not to hit, even gently,
yet parents are effectively handed guns.

459
00:33:24,941 --> 00:33:27,944
What are teachers supposed
to block the bullets with?

460
00:33:28,027 --> 00:33:29,362
Seriously!

461
00:33:30,154 --> 00:33:30,988
Damn it.

462
00:33:31,489 --> 00:33:32,532
In the current system,

463
00:33:33,157 --> 00:33:36,911
if teachers are reported for child abuse,

464
00:33:36,994 --> 00:33:39,038
there's basically no shield
to protect them.

465
00:33:43,876 --> 00:33:45,002
We can be

466
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:47,130
their shield.

467
00:33:47,797 --> 00:33:49,173
Although it will be difficult,

468
00:33:50,258 --> 00:33:51,300
we'll go step by step.

469
00:33:52,552 --> 00:33:53,678
That's what we'll do.

470
00:33:55,263 --> 00:33:56,514
So, Na Hwa-jin.

471
00:33:56,597 --> 00:34:00,476
You just handle the power-abusing parents
hiding behind the law.

472
00:34:12,905 --> 00:34:14,782
I'm getting all fired up to fight.

473
00:34:14,866 --> 00:34:16,159
You've got this!

474
00:34:16,242 --> 00:34:20,288
"You just handle the power-abusing parents
hiding behind the law."

475
00:34:24,876 --> 00:34:25,835
Ms. Choi Ji-seon.

476
00:34:26,335 --> 00:34:27,920
Please come this way.

477
00:34:28,004 --> 00:34:29,172
COUNSELING ROOM

478
00:34:31,424 --> 00:34:32,341
I'll see you soon.

479
00:34:43,102 --> 00:34:46,772
How can a person
harass someone to this extent?

480
00:34:46,856 --> 00:34:48,608
I think people are the scariest.

481
00:34:49,609 --> 00:34:53,446
Still, reptilians are a little scarier.

482
00:34:53,529 --> 00:34:54,363
Rep… what?

483
00:34:54,447 --> 00:34:58,242
There are actually aliens
who have infiltrated Earth right now.

484
00:34:58,326 --> 00:34:59,869
Aliens do not exist.

485
00:34:59,952 --> 00:35:02,997
They really do. There is various evidence
to show reptilian aliens--

486
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:04,957
Seriously, you believe in strange things.

487
00:35:08,085 --> 00:35:11,964
Okay, fine. I'll stop talking now.

488
00:35:12,548 --> 00:35:14,091
Why?

489
00:35:14,175 --> 00:35:16,260
Do I not seem worth talking to anymore?

490
00:35:16,344 --> 00:35:19,722
It feels like my loss

491
00:35:19,805 --> 00:35:22,475
when I talk to people
who are a little ignorant.

492
00:35:23,059 --> 00:35:23,893
I see.

493
00:35:23,976 --> 00:35:25,728
Deputy Director Bong.

494
00:35:25,811 --> 00:35:26,646
Yes?

495
00:35:26,729 --> 00:35:28,439
-The rep…
-Reptilians.

496
00:35:29,106 --> 00:35:31,484
Right, the rep… whatever.

497
00:35:31,567 --> 00:35:32,944
Yes?

498
00:35:33,569 --> 00:35:36,155
Should I show you
that people are scarier than them?

499
00:35:36,864 --> 00:35:37,823
No…

500
00:35:43,788 --> 00:35:44,622
Look.

501
00:35:45,581 --> 00:35:48,960
I'll show you again how to write
the Chinese character for "patience."

502
00:35:49,043 --> 00:35:50,711
It starts with "do" for knife.

503
00:35:51,212 --> 00:35:52,588
Then "sim" for heart.

504
00:35:53,172 --> 00:35:54,882
Cut your heart with a knife.

505
00:35:55,591 --> 00:35:56,467
Try to…

506
00:36:20,199 --> 00:36:23,494
All right,
who would like to solve this problem?

507
00:36:23,577 --> 00:36:24,620
-Me!
-Me!

508
00:36:30,001 --> 00:36:31,168
U-jin, you can try.

509
00:36:35,965 --> 00:36:41,387
<i>In math class, we solved problems</i>
<i>on the board with friends.</i>

510
00:36:41,470 --> 00:36:43,014
<i>Although we taught them,</i>

511
00:36:43,097 --> 00:36:47,101
<i>if anything still needs work,</i>
<i>please review it at home.</i>

512
00:37:00,156 --> 00:37:01,282
Oh my God!

513
00:37:03,409 --> 00:37:04,410
Are you all right?

514
00:37:05,786 --> 00:37:08,539
-Let me help you.
-Why were you standing there?

515
00:37:08,622 --> 00:37:10,207
Well…

516
00:37:10,708 --> 00:37:14,628
This is my classroom,
and I'm the homeroom teacher.

517
00:37:16,047 --> 00:37:18,674
Are you U-jin's new homeroom teacher?

518
00:37:18,758 --> 00:37:20,634
You must be U-jin's mother.

519
00:37:21,218 --> 00:37:23,304
Hello, ma'am.

520
00:37:23,387 --> 00:37:25,890
I'm Na Hwa-jin, U-jin's homeroom teacher.

521
00:37:25,973 --> 00:37:28,684
What brings you here
this early in the morning?

522
00:37:28,768 --> 00:37:31,604
Yesterday, you made U-jin
solve math problems, didn't you?

523
00:37:31,687 --> 00:37:33,981
Yes, but I was so surprised.

524
00:37:34,065 --> 00:37:36,901
How is U-jin so smart?

525
00:37:36,984 --> 00:37:39,445
He seems to have studied ahead.

526
00:37:39,528 --> 00:37:42,156
You had him study ahead a lot, didn't you?

527
00:37:42,239 --> 00:37:43,783
No, not really.

528
00:37:43,866 --> 00:37:46,535
Then he must be a natural.

529
00:37:46,619 --> 00:37:49,580
I wonder if U-jin takes after you.

530
00:37:50,081 --> 00:37:51,832
You did well in school, didn't you?

531
00:37:52,750 --> 00:37:54,335
-A little bit.
-I knew it.

532
00:37:54,418 --> 00:37:57,254
Ma'am, you look like you did.
You really do.

533
00:37:58,839 --> 00:38:03,386
By the way, from now on,
please don't make U-jin solve problems.

534
00:38:03,469 --> 00:38:05,763
If he doesn't know,
it could hurt his self-esteem.

535
00:38:06,347 --> 00:38:08,182
I didn't realize.

536
00:38:08,265 --> 00:38:10,643
I've learned something important
thanks to you.

537
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:14,730
Seeing that we're on the same page,
I won't have to worry this time.

538
00:38:14,814 --> 00:38:16,565
What were you worried about, ma'am?

539
00:38:16,649 --> 00:38:19,068
The previous homeroom teacher
was really strange.

540
00:38:19,151 --> 00:38:22,279
Ma'am, I will make sure
I'm never like that.

541
00:38:23,114 --> 00:38:23,948
Thank you.

542
00:38:27,743 --> 00:38:28,577
NA HWA-JIN

543
00:38:29,537 --> 00:38:31,038
Yes, what can I do for you?

544
00:38:31,122 --> 00:38:34,041
U-jin keeps dozing off during class.

545
00:38:34,125 --> 00:38:35,668
What should I do about it?

546
00:38:35,751 --> 00:38:37,378
You can just wake him.

547
00:38:37,461 --> 00:38:39,755
Sleeping is a student's right.

548
00:38:39,839 --> 00:38:42,800
Would it be okay for me to violate it?

549
00:38:42,883 --> 00:38:44,510
I'll allow it. Just wake him up.

550
00:38:44,593 --> 00:38:45,928
Yes, ma'am.

551
00:38:47,054 --> 00:38:49,056
What would be the best way to wake U-jin?

552
00:38:49,140 --> 00:38:50,433
Just shake him awake.

553
00:38:50,516 --> 00:38:53,185
I could be accused of child abuse
if I touch him.

554
00:38:53,269 --> 00:38:55,521
Then you can just call him to wake him up.

555
00:38:55,604 --> 00:38:56,814
Right!

556
00:38:56,897 --> 00:38:57,773
NA HWA-JIN

557
00:38:57,857 --> 00:39:01,861
If U-jin is startled by the loud noise
and gets emotionally stressed,

558
00:39:01,944 --> 00:39:02,903
that can be abuse…

559
00:39:02,987 --> 00:39:04,822
Then tell his neighbor to wake him.

560
00:39:04,905 --> 00:39:07,116
What if that embarrasses him?

561
00:39:07,199 --> 00:39:09,034
Don't wake him, and just leave him be.

562
00:39:09,118 --> 00:39:12,288
Ma'am, that would be neglect.
Neglect is also a form of abuse.

563
00:39:14,832 --> 00:39:16,917
<i>Hello? Ma'am?</i>

564
00:39:17,668 --> 00:39:18,711
NA HWA-JIN

565
00:39:22,882 --> 00:39:24,091
For God's sake.

566
00:39:31,765 --> 00:39:32,933
<i>Ma'am, it's me.</i>

567
00:39:33,017 --> 00:39:37,605
<i>When marking U-jin's spelling tests,</i>
<i>what should I use instead of a slash?</i>

568
00:39:38,105 --> 00:39:39,773
There are so many options.

569
00:39:39,857 --> 00:39:41,192
You could use a star.

570
00:39:41,275 --> 00:39:44,361
<i>But stars are used for important things.</i>

571
00:39:44,445 --> 00:39:45,321
Or a triangle.

572
00:39:45,404 --> 00:39:48,908
<i>That's for partially correct answers.</i>

573
00:39:51,952 --> 00:39:52,786
A rhombus?

574
00:39:52,870 --> 00:39:53,787
A trapezoid.

575
00:39:54,288 --> 00:39:55,289
NA HWA-JIN

576
00:39:55,372 --> 00:39:56,332
Just…

577
00:39:58,292 --> 00:39:59,752
use a slash.

578
00:39:59,835 --> 00:40:01,587
<i>Yes, ma'am. I'll call you again.</i>

579
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:02,922
Damn it.

580
00:40:03,964 --> 00:40:05,049
Goddamn it!

581
00:40:10,679 --> 00:40:12,097
<i>What are your thoughts</i>

582
00:40:12,181 --> 00:40:15,142
on parents contacting teachers

583
00:40:15,226 --> 00:40:17,061
on their personal numbers?

584
00:40:17,144 --> 00:40:21,357
I heard it has major implications
for teachers' rights and privacy.

585
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:26,111
That's why we're running a pilot project
to provide work numbers for teachers.

586
00:40:26,195 --> 00:40:27,446
Will it be effective?

587
00:40:28,322 --> 00:40:30,032
Can parents actually be stopped

588
00:40:30,115 --> 00:40:34,370
from contacting teachers on social media,
via DMs, or even visiting their homes?

589
00:40:35,162 --> 00:40:38,249
We plan to set up
a complaints response team in each school

590
00:40:38,332 --> 00:40:41,627
to save teachers
from directly dealing with complaints.

591
00:40:41,710 --> 00:40:44,463
Are you saying it's fine for them
to deal with complaints?

592
00:40:44,964 --> 00:40:46,340
They're not punching bags.

593
00:40:46,423 --> 00:40:50,177
Passing complaints around
will only create another tragedy.

594
00:40:53,264 --> 00:40:56,350
You say you'll change the system
and find a solution

595
00:40:56,850 --> 00:40:59,144
every time a teacher dies at school.

596
00:40:59,228 --> 00:41:01,939
Then this should stop happening,
but why hasn't it?

597
00:41:02,022 --> 00:41:04,483
A system isn't something
you create after an incident.

598
00:41:04,567 --> 00:41:06,652
It's something you design
to prevent problems.

599
00:41:09,530 --> 00:41:11,240
Let's come up with a solution.

600
00:41:11,740 --> 00:41:14,660
If the law is needed,
I'll bring in the Minister of Justice.

601
00:41:14,743 --> 00:41:17,580
If power is needed,
I'll bring the president if I have to.

602
00:41:17,663 --> 00:41:18,706
Let's make sure

603
00:41:19,373 --> 00:41:21,292
no more teachers die

604
00:41:21,792 --> 00:41:23,210
because of complaints.

605
00:41:23,919 --> 00:41:24,962
Yes, sir.

606
00:41:38,225 --> 00:41:39,602
Ma'am!

607
00:41:39,685 --> 00:41:41,604
I was actually about to call you.

608
00:41:41,687 --> 00:41:44,815
When we wave to greet others,
we wave like this.

609
00:41:44,898 --> 00:41:48,068
Should I get the kids
to use their right hand or left hand?

610
00:41:48,152 --> 00:41:51,196
Waving is actually related
to the right and left sides of the brain.

611
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:53,741
That's something
you can decide for yourself.

612
00:41:53,824 --> 00:41:56,994
What would a teacher know?
You would know better.

613
00:41:57,077 --> 00:41:59,496
Then what would teachers be at school for?

614
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:01,915
I'll call you when I need to,
so please don't call.

615
00:42:02,875 --> 00:42:04,710
Then maybe I could DM you or--

616
00:42:04,793 --> 00:42:07,129
No, I'm telling you not to!

617
00:42:07,713 --> 00:42:09,882
-Yes, ma'am.
-And watch yourself.

618
00:42:10,382 --> 00:42:12,718
My husband is furious
about what happened yesterday.

619
00:42:12,801 --> 00:42:14,219
U-jin's father?

620
00:42:14,887 --> 00:42:16,639
Oh no. That shouldn't happen.

621
00:42:21,769 --> 00:42:23,979
Customer number 820.

622
00:42:24,688 --> 00:42:25,731
Yes.

623
00:42:25,814 --> 00:42:27,149
-Hello.
-Here.

624
00:42:27,232 --> 00:42:28,734
How can I help you?

625
00:42:28,817 --> 00:42:31,111
May I please speak to U-jin's father?

626
00:42:32,112 --> 00:42:33,113
Pardon?

627
00:42:34,114 --> 00:42:35,407
U-jin's father.

628
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:37,660
U-jin's father.

629
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,370
There's a second floor.

630
00:42:39,453 --> 00:42:41,288
U-jin's father!

631
00:42:41,372 --> 00:42:42,831
U-jin's fath…

632
00:42:47,211 --> 00:42:50,089
-Who are you?
-Do you happen to be U-jin's father?

633
00:42:50,923 --> 00:42:51,840
Yes, I am.

634
00:42:55,094 --> 00:42:58,138
Sir, I am very sorry.

635
00:42:58,222 --> 00:42:59,765
Please forgive me just this once.

636
00:42:59,848 --> 00:43:00,808
Please don't do this.

637
00:43:00,891 --> 00:43:04,436
I worked very hard
to become a teacher, sir.

638
00:43:05,396 --> 00:43:07,022
Are you U-jin's homeroom teacher?

639
00:43:07,106 --> 00:43:10,651
I heard you were extremely angry
because of what I did, sir.

640
00:43:10,734 --> 00:43:15,864
If you tell me what I did wrong,
I will make sure it never happens again.

641
00:43:16,865 --> 00:43:18,283
-Please just get up.
-Sir!

642
00:43:18,367 --> 00:43:20,452
Sir, is it because I put a slash

643
00:43:20,536 --> 00:43:22,955
through U-jin's wrong answers like this

644
00:43:23,455 --> 00:43:25,124
that you are so angry?

645
00:43:25,207 --> 00:43:26,417
If that's not it,

646
00:43:26,500 --> 00:43:30,629
is it because I used negative words
such as "no" and "don't" to U-jin?

647
00:43:30,713 --> 00:43:34,466
The last time you came to our school,
you almost hit the former teacher.

648
00:43:34,550 --> 00:43:36,844
It serves us right to get beaten up, sir.

649
00:43:36,927 --> 00:43:38,470
But you'll get me fired.

650
00:43:38,554 --> 00:43:40,806
Please don't take away my livelihood, sir.

651
00:43:41,974 --> 00:43:44,184
Sir, I'm begging you.

652
00:43:44,268 --> 00:43:46,478
-Let go of me.
-Gosh, please don't hit…

653
00:43:46,562 --> 00:43:47,771
-Oh my.
-What's with him?

654
00:43:48,772 --> 00:43:50,649
Sir, I am sorry.

655
00:43:51,316 --> 00:43:52,818
Sir, it's not what you think.

656
00:43:52,901 --> 00:43:54,069
Sir!

657
00:43:54,153 --> 00:43:56,238
Oh my God. How embarrassing.
What is he doing?

658
00:43:56,321 --> 00:43:57,781
-Seriously?
-Sir!

659
00:43:59,366 --> 00:44:00,200
Your pants, sir.

660
00:44:01,076 --> 00:44:02,286
-Pull your pants up.
-Damn.

661
00:44:02,369 --> 00:44:03,203
Wait.

662
00:44:03,954 --> 00:44:05,706
Do you have a death wish?

663
00:44:12,921 --> 00:44:14,715
Learn to control that temper of yours.

664
00:44:15,507 --> 00:44:19,052
If I ever hear anything
like "my husband is angry" again,

665
00:44:20,888 --> 00:44:21,847
then you're done for.

666
00:44:27,561 --> 00:44:28,645
Right then, sir.

667
00:44:29,146 --> 00:44:30,773
I'll get going now, sir.

668
00:44:33,108 --> 00:44:34,151
Damn it!

669
00:44:34,651 --> 00:44:37,571
That was embarrassing as hell!
Can't you even handle one teacher?

670
00:44:37,654 --> 00:44:39,072
How did I know he'd do that?

671
00:44:40,449 --> 00:44:43,285
I'm up for a promotion soon.
The manager saw everything. Now what?

672
00:44:43,368 --> 00:44:45,954
It was that teacher.
Why take it out on me?

673
00:44:46,038 --> 00:44:47,080
Damn you!

674
00:44:47,164 --> 00:44:48,373
You deal with this.

675
00:44:48,457 --> 00:44:50,667
Talk to the principal,
or file a complaint.

676
00:44:50,751 --> 00:44:52,169
Get the bastard fired now!

677
00:44:52,252 --> 00:44:53,337
Fine!

678
00:44:53,420 --> 00:44:54,588
Jesus.

679
00:44:55,297 --> 00:44:56,256
Damn it.

680
00:45:00,552 --> 00:45:02,888
-Hello.
-Hi, guys.

681
00:45:04,056 --> 00:45:06,099
-Hello.
-Bye, Mom.

682
00:45:06,183 --> 00:45:08,227
-Hi, children.
-Hello.

683
00:45:13,482 --> 00:45:15,859
Do you even train your teachers?

684
00:45:15,943 --> 00:45:18,320
Mr. Na caused a scene
at a parent's workplace!

685
00:45:18,403 --> 00:45:19,530
Do something.

686
00:45:23,826 --> 00:45:26,245
It's illegal for you to show up like this.

687
00:45:26,328 --> 00:45:28,831
If you would like to contact us,
use the app.

688
00:45:29,331 --> 00:45:32,709
And if you have a complaint,
please follow the proper procedure.

689
00:45:33,418 --> 00:45:34,920
If that's not enough,

690
00:45:35,003 --> 00:45:38,090
please use an online complaint board
at the Blue House,

691
00:45:38,173 --> 00:45:41,343
the Ministry of Education, or the ERPB.

692
00:45:41,927 --> 00:45:43,136
Ma'am.

693
00:45:43,220 --> 00:45:45,138
Do you think I don't know that already?

694
00:45:45,222 --> 00:45:48,559
Shall I tell you something else
you already know very well?

695
00:45:48,642 --> 00:45:50,894
U-jin may be your precious child,

696
00:45:51,937 --> 00:45:54,898
but the teachers are also

697
00:45:55,399 --> 00:45:57,359
someone's precious child.

698
00:46:01,613 --> 00:46:03,031
You're all

699
00:46:03,824 --> 00:46:05,242
out of your minds.

700
00:46:05,325 --> 00:46:07,995
You'll regret this. Just you wait.

701
00:46:18,422 --> 00:46:20,299
<i>The ERPB will take responsibility</i>

702
00:46:20,883 --> 00:46:22,593
and deal with any consequences.

703
00:46:22,676 --> 00:46:24,761
So when things like this happen,

704
00:46:25,345 --> 00:46:29,266
please be the teachers' mentor,
not their principal.

705
00:46:31,435 --> 00:46:34,646
Right now, the teachers need

706
00:46:34,730 --> 00:46:36,815
a mentor like you…

707
00:46:38,817 --> 00:46:40,611
more than they need the ERPB.

708
00:46:54,499 --> 00:46:55,542
He's right.

709
00:46:57,544 --> 00:46:58,837
We were their mentors.

710
00:47:02,257 --> 00:47:03,258
Sometimes,

711
00:47:04,676 --> 00:47:06,178
I seem to forget.

712
00:47:13,143 --> 00:47:14,603
What have you drawn here?

713
00:47:15,395 --> 00:47:16,939
U-jin, come with me.

714
00:47:17,606 --> 00:47:18,440
We're done here.

715
00:47:20,776 --> 00:47:21,818
Get up.

716
00:47:27,950 --> 00:47:29,034
Get up!

717
00:47:39,836 --> 00:47:41,254
Gather the parents for me.

718
00:47:41,338 --> 00:47:43,507
This is absurd.
I'll tell you when we meet.

719
00:47:51,807 --> 00:47:53,517
You're all here.

720
00:48:02,317 --> 00:48:04,027
Why are you here?

721
00:48:04,111 --> 00:48:05,612
Hello, ma'am.

722
00:48:06,154 --> 00:48:07,155
Well…

723
00:48:11,118 --> 00:48:12,744
I came to give you this.

724
00:48:13,328 --> 00:48:14,705
What is this?

725
00:48:14,788 --> 00:48:16,832
If you take a look…

726
00:48:18,083 --> 00:48:20,377
COMPLAINT
COMPLAINANT: NA HWA-JIN

727
00:48:20,460 --> 00:48:24,089
I filed a complaint against you
for child abuse.

728
00:48:24,172 --> 00:48:25,841
-Child abuse?
-Yes.

729
00:48:25,924 --> 00:48:27,300
I saw everything.

730
00:48:27,884 --> 00:48:30,012
U-jin didn't want to,

731
00:48:30,095 --> 00:48:32,014
but you grabbed him
and held him like this.

732
00:48:32,097 --> 00:48:36,018
When he was changing into his gym clothes,
he had bruises all over his body and--

733
00:48:36,101 --> 00:48:37,352
Where on my child's body

734
00:48:38,812 --> 00:48:40,313
are you saying there are bruises?

735
00:48:40,397 --> 00:48:43,859
Well, we'll find out
once the police investigate.

736
00:48:43,942 --> 00:48:46,945
What gives you the right
to report me, his parent?

737
00:48:47,029 --> 00:48:50,157
"When a teacher becomes aware of
or suspects child abuse

738
00:48:50,240 --> 00:48:53,118
in the course of performing their duties,

739
00:48:53,201 --> 00:48:55,120
the teacher shall immediately report it

740
00:48:55,203 --> 00:48:57,831
to a child protection agency
or an investigative agency."

741
00:48:58,790 --> 00:48:59,750
That's the law.

742
00:49:00,542 --> 00:49:01,918
What if it's not child abuse?

743
00:49:02,711 --> 00:49:04,171
Then I'll have to apologize.

744
00:49:05,630 --> 00:49:07,591
That's the law.

745
00:49:13,972 --> 00:49:17,392
I heard this mom
bullied Ms. Choi Ji-seon, didn't she?

746
00:49:17,476 --> 00:49:21,229
It was so bad, the teacher developed
partial facial paralysis.

747
00:49:21,813 --> 00:49:24,024
She's not well enough
to come to school now.

748
00:49:24,107 --> 00:49:25,484
-Really?
-I knew it.

749
00:49:25,567 --> 00:49:27,819
I heard she's been extreme
since kindergarten.

750
00:49:27,903 --> 00:49:29,696
No wonder the kid is odd.

751
00:49:29,780 --> 00:49:32,032
Yes, it's a relief
he's not in my child's class.

752
00:49:32,115 --> 00:49:33,658
-I know, right?
-Who said that?

753
00:49:34,159 --> 00:49:35,702
U-jin's mom.

754
00:49:35,786 --> 00:49:36,953
I asked who said that.

755
00:49:37,037 --> 00:49:39,706
No one said it. On the Internet, it…

756
00:49:39,790 --> 00:49:41,166
Was it that bitch, Ms. Choi?

757
00:49:43,210 --> 00:49:44,836
-I'm asking you!
-Oh my.

758
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:46,963
Was it that bitch of a teacher,
Choi Ji-seon?

759
00:49:48,840 --> 00:49:49,800
So-yun.

760
00:49:49,883 --> 00:49:52,135
-Let's go.
-I'd better go too.

761
00:49:57,307 --> 00:50:00,644
U-JIN'S MOTHER

762
00:50:19,037 --> 00:50:20,497
Damn it.

763
00:50:21,706 --> 00:50:22,624
Damn it.

764
00:51:02,247 --> 00:51:03,832
Were you two in on it together?

765
00:51:05,876 --> 00:51:08,461
Don't you know U-jin is being left out
because of you?

766
00:51:08,545 --> 00:51:10,964
Why the hell is the teacher at fault?
That's on you.

767
00:51:11,047 --> 00:51:12,007
Excuse me?

768
00:51:12,090 --> 00:51:14,342
-Are you being rude to a parent right now?
-What?

769
00:51:14,426 --> 00:51:16,219
You're rude. Why can't I be?

770
00:51:17,888 --> 00:51:21,766
I'll report you and that bitch
to the Office of Education and the press.

771
00:51:21,850 --> 00:51:23,268
Oh, and the ERPB.

772
00:51:23,810 --> 00:51:25,395
My family works there.

773
00:51:25,979 --> 00:51:28,148
I'll see to it that you never teach again.

774
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:31,359
Allow me to reintroduce myself.

775
00:51:32,652 --> 00:51:35,405
I'm Inspector Na Hwa-jin from the ERPB.

776
00:51:36,740 --> 00:51:39,826
I am well aware of what you did
to Ms. Choi.

777
00:51:39,910 --> 00:51:41,244
That's why we are here.

778
00:51:41,328 --> 00:51:42,412
Isn't this entrapment?

779
00:51:43,371 --> 00:51:45,081
Entrapment is illegal!

780
00:51:45,165 --> 00:51:46,917
You love the law, don't you?

781
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,210
Shall we do it legally?

782
00:51:48,293 --> 00:51:50,545
The ERPB investigation finds you liable

783
00:51:50,629 --> 00:51:53,632
of criminal penalties
for malicious false complaints,

784
00:51:53,715 --> 00:51:55,342
violation of teachers' rights,

785
00:51:55,425 --> 00:51:57,344
obstruction of business, and insult.

786
00:51:57,427 --> 00:51:58,845
What did I do wrong?

787
00:51:58,929 --> 00:52:00,805
It was all for my child's sake.

788
00:52:00,889 --> 00:52:04,517
What kind of parent in the world
would just watch their child being harmed?

789
00:52:04,601 --> 00:52:06,895
It's all Choi's fault.

790
00:52:06,978 --> 00:52:08,939
What does she know about education
with no kids?

791
00:52:09,814 --> 00:52:11,816
How would she know how a parent feels?

792
00:52:14,778 --> 00:52:18,114
Then you'd know very well
how Ms. Choi's parents feel.

793
00:52:19,241 --> 00:52:23,245
How do you think her mother felt
watching her daughter suffer?

794
00:52:24,955 --> 00:52:25,789
I don't know.

795
00:52:26,289 --> 00:52:28,124
Who cares what happens to that bitch?

796
00:52:28,625 --> 00:52:30,085
Only my child matters to me.

797
00:52:30,669 --> 00:52:32,754
All the parents in the world are the same.

798
00:52:37,300 --> 00:52:39,970
Are you sure this looks like me?

799
00:52:40,595 --> 00:52:42,264
Are you? Wait.

800
00:52:42,347 --> 00:52:47,394
I don't think the skin tone
matches mine, U-jin.

801
00:52:48,645 --> 00:52:50,105
I'll draw too.

802
00:52:52,607 --> 00:52:53,566
U-jin.

803
00:52:54,985 --> 00:52:59,072
Why did you call me on your mom's phone?

804
00:52:59,572 --> 00:53:01,658
You told me

805
00:53:01,741 --> 00:53:04,077
I should do what my heart tells me.

806
00:53:04,828 --> 00:53:08,707
I was having a hard time,
so I wanted to see you.

807
00:53:12,377 --> 00:53:14,963
Why were you having a hard time?

808
00:53:18,341 --> 00:53:20,343
I'm sorry, Ms. Choi.

809
00:53:20,844 --> 00:53:23,680
My mom hurt you a lot, didn't she?

810
00:53:28,518 --> 00:53:29,602
U-jin.

811
00:53:31,771 --> 00:53:33,440
It's not up to you to apologize.

812
00:53:40,071 --> 00:53:42,699
HOME OF THE HEART

813
00:53:42,782 --> 00:53:44,951
Mom hates me.

814
00:53:45,618 --> 00:53:47,620
She doesn't smile at me

815
00:53:47,704 --> 00:53:49,706
and always looks angry.

816
00:53:53,960 --> 00:53:55,253
Come here, U-jin.

817
00:53:58,965 --> 00:54:02,510
You must have had a really tough time.

818
00:54:03,011 --> 00:54:04,137
It's okay.

819
00:54:05,221 --> 00:54:06,890
It's all right.

820
00:54:11,102 --> 00:54:12,312
You're okay.

821
00:54:21,154 --> 00:54:22,906
Do you feel a little better now?

822
00:54:25,241 --> 00:54:27,243
Shall we get back to coloring this in?

823
00:54:33,625 --> 00:54:36,086
Who do you think
truly cares for the child?

824
00:54:43,176 --> 00:54:46,304
What kind of adult
do you hope U-jin grows up to be?

825
00:54:47,180 --> 00:54:50,809
The kind who does not apologize,
even when he's wrong?

826
00:54:52,060 --> 00:54:55,980
The kind who lives a lonely life
with no friends or colleagues?

827
00:54:58,900 --> 00:55:03,154
The kind who treats others' lives
as worthless if it serves their own gain?

828
00:55:03,822 --> 00:55:05,407
That's not what you want.

829
00:55:06,324 --> 00:55:07,992
So please stop.

830
00:55:08,827 --> 00:55:10,578
Your child doesn't like it.

831
00:55:11,079 --> 00:55:12,997
He says he likes his teacher.

832
00:55:13,498 --> 00:55:14,874
Please trust U-jin

833
00:55:16,251 --> 00:55:18,002
and trust his teacher.

834
00:55:20,046 --> 00:55:23,133
Hey, you can't draw it like this.

835
00:55:24,342 --> 00:55:25,844
Do you think it looks like me?

836
00:55:27,011 --> 00:55:27,929
Do you?

837
00:55:28,012 --> 00:55:30,265
Why can't you answer me, U-jin?

838
00:55:31,057 --> 00:55:32,308
I think it looks like me.

839
00:55:32,392 --> 00:55:35,311
I'll be the rabbit. You be the bear.

840
00:55:41,359 --> 00:55:42,861
That's a great drawing.

841
00:55:47,657 --> 00:55:50,702
How did you know
Ms. Choi would come to the school?

842
00:55:50,785 --> 00:55:52,078
Because she's a teacher.

843
00:55:52,829 --> 00:55:54,622
School came to my mind first.

844
00:55:55,707 --> 00:55:57,750
I guess it was the same for Ms. Choi too.

845
00:55:57,834 --> 00:56:00,295
So you two were telepathic.

846
00:56:00,378 --> 00:56:02,088
Maybe.

847
00:56:02,922 --> 00:56:06,050
By any chance,
do you both know what telepathy is?

848
00:56:06,134 --> 00:56:08,344
Isn't it when you think the same
as someone else?

849
00:56:08,428 --> 00:56:10,388
No, it's not simply thinking the same.

850
00:56:10,472 --> 00:56:12,932
It's when a person's thoughts and actions

851
00:56:13,016 --> 00:56:15,852
are passed on to someone else.

852
00:56:15,935 --> 00:56:18,021
It's like a kind of superpower.

853
00:56:18,104 --> 00:56:20,815
They're just lucky guesses.
A superpower is a stretch.

854
00:56:20,899 --> 00:56:22,609
No, telepathy is really real.

855
00:56:22,692 --> 00:56:24,694
-Can you prove it?
-Of course.

856
00:56:25,278 --> 00:56:26,112
Okay, then.

857
00:56:26,654 --> 00:56:29,908
Look into my eyes and think of a word.
I'll guess what it is.

858
00:56:29,991 --> 00:56:31,201
For God's sake.

859
00:56:43,087 --> 00:56:44,088
Done. Take a guess.

860
00:56:46,508 --> 00:56:47,342
Eye booger.

861
00:56:47,926 --> 00:56:49,511
What? Eye booger?

862
00:56:50,011 --> 00:56:52,722
You're wrong. You didn't get it.
You can't do anything.

863
00:56:53,223 --> 00:56:56,893
No, I meant
you've got a huge eye booger in there.

864
00:57:00,688 --> 00:57:02,941
You have an eye booger.
That's embarrassing.

865
00:57:03,024 --> 00:57:04,025
I've got it out.

866
00:57:05,985 --> 00:57:07,278
So what do you want to eat?

867
00:57:07,362 --> 00:57:08,446
-<i>Jokbal</i>.
-<i>Jokbal </i>or…

868
00:57:08,947 --> 00:57:10,573
Oh wow.

869
00:57:10,657 --> 00:57:13,076
Amazing. This is what I'm talking about.

870
00:57:13,159 --> 00:57:15,036
That's the word I thought of earlier.

871
00:57:15,119 --> 00:57:16,663
Now, that's telepathy.

872
00:57:16,746 --> 00:57:18,498
See? I told you it's real.

873
00:57:18,581 --> 00:57:19,541
Try it again.

874
00:57:19,624 --> 00:57:22,460
This time, think of a color…

875
00:57:22,544 --> 00:57:25,505
Let's assume there are two people,
A and B.

876
00:57:26,172 --> 00:57:30,343
A used their position to threaten B,

877
00:57:30,426 --> 00:57:32,554
obstruct B's exercise of rights,

878
00:57:32,637 --> 00:57:34,639
and force B to do things
outside their role.

879
00:57:35,223 --> 00:57:38,184
<i>This falls under Article 324,</i>
<i>Paragraph 1 of the Criminal Act</i>

880
00:57:38,268 --> 00:57:41,688
<i>as a crime of coercion and is punishable</i>
<i>by up to five years' imprisonment</i>

881
00:57:41,771 --> 00:57:43,481
or a fine of up to 30 million won.

882
00:57:43,565 --> 00:57:44,399
DEFENDANT

883
00:57:44,482 --> 00:57:45,358
Furthermore,

884
00:57:45,858 --> 00:57:49,529
A kept snooping on B's social media,
left malicious comments,

885
00:57:49,612 --> 00:57:51,489
<i>and even commented on B's underwear,</i>

886
00:57:51,573 --> 00:57:54,325
<i>causing B to feel disgust</i>
<i>and sexual humiliation.</i>

887
00:57:54,409 --> 00:57:58,413
A persistently messaged B
and turned up at B's home,

888
00:57:58,496 --> 00:58:01,457
causing B to feel fear and anxiety.

889
00:58:01,958 --> 00:58:05,253
This can constitute stalking
and is a crime

890
00:58:05,336 --> 00:58:07,672
under the Punishment
of Crime of Stalking Act,

891
00:58:07,755 --> 00:58:10,717
punishable by
up to three years' imprisonment

892
00:58:10,800 --> 00:58:12,093
or a fine of 30 million won.

893
00:58:13,011 --> 00:58:15,597
Moreover, with the intent to induce fear,

894
00:58:15,680 --> 00:58:19,684
person A utilized an acquaintance
to attempt an assault on person B,

895
00:58:19,767 --> 00:58:23,605
which falls under Article 283,
Paragraph 1 of the Criminal Act.

896
00:58:24,188 --> 00:58:28,735
This is subject to a fine of up to
five million won or three years in prison.

897
00:58:33,906 --> 00:58:37,452
With such conduct ongoing,
B fell into depression,

898
00:58:37,535 --> 00:58:39,329
<i>suffered a nervous breakdown,</i>

899
00:58:39,412 --> 00:58:41,831
<i>and even made an extreme decision</i>
<i>to harm themselves.</i>

900
00:58:42,790 --> 00:58:44,584
This is also an undeniable crime,

901
00:58:44,667 --> 00:58:48,379
constituting assault and battery,
causing bodily harm.

902
00:58:50,757 --> 00:58:52,717
A is the defendant,

903
00:58:53,217 --> 00:58:54,052
and B is

904
00:58:55,178 --> 00:58:56,387
Ms. Choi Ji-seon.

905
00:59:00,975 --> 00:59:03,686
These actions are undeniable crimes

906
00:59:03,770 --> 00:59:05,980
when they occur between persons.

907
00:59:06,648 --> 00:59:09,442
So why are they allowed
between a teacher and a parent?

908
00:59:20,161 --> 00:59:21,704
<i>We have learned</i>

909
00:59:21,788 --> 00:59:24,832
that repeated, constant,
and malicious parental complaints

910
00:59:24,916 --> 00:59:27,293
place undue pressure on innocent teachers

911
00:59:27,377 --> 00:59:31,756
and even deprive them of the opportunity
to become good teachers.

912
00:59:31,839 --> 00:59:34,384
In the future,
when a teacher is reported for child abuse

913
00:59:34,467 --> 00:59:36,177
or a malicious complaint is filed,

914
00:59:36,260 --> 00:59:39,430
the ERPB will dispatch
an inspector on-site

915
00:59:39,514 --> 00:59:41,766
to determine the facts.

916
00:59:41,849 --> 00:59:43,643
If the teacher is found innocent,

917
00:59:44,310 --> 00:59:48,398
we promise to fight together
with the teachers.

918
00:59:49,399 --> 00:59:54,028
As the term "teacher-student relationship"
loses its meaning in today's age,

919
00:59:54,112 --> 00:59:56,447
we ask parents to cooperate

920
00:59:56,531 --> 01:00:00,410
so that the few remaining true educators
do not end up leaving the profession.

921
01:00:01,077 --> 01:00:04,497
We will also establish an annual
health check-up system for teachers,

922
01:00:04,580 --> 01:00:07,166
which will include support and treatment

923
01:00:07,250 --> 01:00:10,753
for those experiencing
psychological difficulties.

924
01:00:27,770 --> 01:00:29,439
To the teachers

925
01:00:29,939 --> 01:00:32,942
who ended their own lives
due to teachers' rights violations

926
01:00:33,443 --> 01:00:34,569
and

927
01:00:35,611 --> 01:00:38,656
to the teachers
who are currently suffering,

928
01:00:39,574 --> 01:00:43,161
on behalf of the Ministry of Education,

929
01:00:44,078 --> 01:00:45,621
I offer my sincere apology.

930
01:00:47,331 --> 01:00:49,375
Due to the failures
of the educational system,

931
01:00:50,042 --> 01:00:51,544
you were left unprotected…

932
01:00:53,963 --> 01:00:55,840
and were made to suffer in silence.

933
01:00:56,799 --> 01:00:58,134
I apologize.

934
01:01:21,032 --> 01:01:23,201
That's it. Well done.

935
01:01:25,745 --> 01:01:26,871
Can you receive…

936
01:01:30,750 --> 01:01:32,460
Yes!

937
01:02:25,346 --> 01:02:27,181
MOCK CSAT
PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT SUPPLIES

938
01:02:27,265 --> 01:02:29,725
MIDTERM EXAM MARKING
OPEN CLASS PREPARATION

939
01:02:32,562 --> 01:02:34,981
WEDDING DAY

940
01:02:38,442 --> 01:02:41,112
IT'S BEEN TWO WEEKS
SINCE COMING TO SCHOOL WITH GYU-CHEOL

941
01:02:41,195 --> 01:02:42,655
MY HEART FELT HEAVY THIS MORNING

942
01:02:42,738 --> 01:02:44,073
GYU-CHEOL HAS BEEN ON MY MIND

943
01:02:45,199 --> 01:02:47,785
WE HAD CAREERS COUNSELING
BUT GYU-CHEOL HAS NO DREAMS

944
01:02:56,836 --> 01:03:00,172
WHAT SHOULD I DO… ABOUT GYU-CHEOL?

945
01:03:05,094 --> 01:03:10,141
WILL I EVER BE ABLE TO… FORGIVE GYU-CHEOL?

946
01:04:15,790 --> 01:04:18,751
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

